<ns4720:note xmlns:ns4720="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.concepts.architecture.organizational.strategies.reliability.sixSigma.overview.overview">
  <ns4721:title xmlns:ns4721="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Six Sigma for reducing process variation</ns4721:title>
  <ns4722:para xmlns:ns4722="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      Six sigma is a quality management approach developed by Motorola
    (see for example <ns4723:xref xmlns:ns4723="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" linkend="Pande-Neumann-Cavanaugh-2000"/>). 
    It is meant to provide a framework for continuous process optimization in order to eliminate
    process defects.
  </ns4722:para>  
  <ns4724:para xmlns:ns4724="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    Six-sigma is based on the following six pillars:
    <ns4725:itemizedlist xmlns:ns4725="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      <ns4726:listitem xmlns:ns4726="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4727:formalpara xmlns:ns4727="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns4728:title xmlns:ns4728="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Visualize</ns4728:title>
        <ns4729:para xmlns:ns4729="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          where one improves ones understanding of customer, business and benchmark goals and performs
          an initial gap analysis to understand how far one is from achieving these,
        </ns4729:para>
      </ns4727:formalpara></ns4726:listitem>
      <ns4730:listitem xmlns:ns4730="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4731:formalpara xmlns:ns4731="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns4732:title xmlns:ns4732="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Commit</ns4732:title>
        <ns4733:para xmlns:ns4733="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          where the various parties commit to making the changes required to achieve these goals. This may
          include team building negotiation and contract renegotiation.
        </ns4733:para>
      </ns4731:formalpara></ns4730:listitem>
      <ns4734:listitem xmlns:ns4734="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4735:formalpara xmlns:ns4735="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns4736:title xmlns:ns4736="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Prioritization</ns4736:title>
        <ns4737:para xmlns:ns4737="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          which includes refining the gap analysis, task prioritization, project planning,
        </ns4737:para>
      </ns4735:formalpara></ns4734:listitem>
      <ns4738:listitem xmlns:ns4738="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4739:formalpara xmlns:ns4739="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns4740:title xmlns:ns4740="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Characterization</ns4740:title>
        <ns4741:para xmlns:ns4741="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          which includes root cause, value stream, capacity and risk analysis, process flow characterization and metrics,
        </ns4741:para>
      </ns4739:formalpara></ns4738:listitem>
      <ns4742:listitem xmlns:ns4742="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4743:formalpara xmlns:ns4743="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns4744:title xmlns:ns4744="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Improvement</ns4744:title>
        <ns4745:para xmlns:ns4745="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          which covers improvement of organizational architecture, business process workflows, and
          quality processes and metrics, deployment of these processes and training,
        </ns4745:para>
      </ns4743:formalpara></ns4742:listitem>
      <ns4746:listitem xmlns:ns4746="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4747:formalpara xmlns:ns4747="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns4748:title xmlns:ns4748="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Achieve</ns4748:title>
        <ns4749:para xmlns:ns4749="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          which includes improvement of the deployment metrics, communication including sharing of the lessons learnt
          and updated best practices across the organization.
        </ns4749:para>
      </ns4747:formalpara></ns4746:listitem>
    </ns4725:itemizedlist>
  </ns4724:para>
</ns4720:note>